Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the macaroni.

Meanwhile, trim the @Brussels sprouts{200%grams}. Quarter them through the root, then pop them onto a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until browned and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @macaroni{180%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Heat a drizzle of oil in another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

When the onion has about 5 mins remaining, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams} to the pan and stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

While the onion and bacon cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%grams}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{25%grams}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb.

Season with salt and pepper, then set your cheesy crumb aside.

Once the onion is cooked, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Melt in the @butter{20%grams}, then stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @water{250%milliliters} a little at a time, followed by the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}. Bring to the boil, then stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%grams} and @Dijon mustard{10%grams} into the sauce (add less mustard if you prefer), then remove from the heat. Stir through the Cheddar until melted, then season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, turn your #grill{} on to high.

Once the Brussels sprouts and macaroni are cooked, gently stir them through the cheese sauce. Add a splash of water if it needs loosening a little.

Transfer the mac & cheese to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle over the cheesy crumb.

Once hot, grill until golden and bubbling, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When ready, allow it to stand for a couple of minutes before sharing between your bowls.

Enjoy!